result.execSummary:
The deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Andras King in court.  Attorney Dawn Marie Rablin in court for Andras King.  Prosecuting attorney David T. Malone in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
The defendant has complied with the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.  On motion of the State, Court ordered case dismissed with prejudice.  Bail to be returned if applicable.
DPA Supervision Report, received and filed

Defendant Andras King in court with attorney Amanda M. Parent.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant in compliance with the terms of the agreement. Court scheduled final review hearing with parties. Case adjourned to Branch 17.  Review hearing scheduled for October 31, 2022 at 09:10 am.
Received and Filed, DPA Supervision Report 8.1.2022

As a condition of bail, court order the defendant may not possess dangerous weapons or firearms or apply for a conceal carry permit.
Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.
Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Parties are prepared to enter into a deferred prosecution agreement.

Defendant was advised of constitution rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Complaint/Information.  Court WITHHELD entry of judgment of conviction.  Deferred Prosecution Agreement received and filed.

Parties not able to sign plea questionnaire and agreement due to current circumstances. Court accepts verbal agreement from all parties.
 
Court ordered case adjourned for Review in Branch 21.

Case set for a Preliminary Hearing. Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing. Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Court held colloquy with defendant. Probable cause has been found and the defendant is bound over for trial.  Original Information e-filed, copy given to defense counsel who waived reading. Defense enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of the defendant.

Defendant Andras King in court with attorney Amanda M. Parent.  Karen Lynch Vespalec appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: AMI
  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defense waived reading and momentarily enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of client.  Review hearing scheduled for August 1, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
